Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
recreatePtnCellBlockage(25.10)                  recreatePtnCellBlockage(25.10)

Name
       recreatePtnCellBlockage  - Recreates cell blockage for a specified par-
       tition, or all partitions

Syntax
       recreatePtnCellBlockage

       [-help]

       [<ptnName>]

       [-noPinCutSpace | -hasPinCutSpace]

       [-noViaCutSpace | -hasViaCutSpace]

       Recreates cell blockage for a specified partition, or  all  partitions.
       This  reflects  incremental  changes, such as pin movement. You can use
       this command after editing the pin in a partition with the Pin  Editor,
       or using the editPin command, to move pins in the partition.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each recreatePtnCellBlockage  parameter.  For  a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command: man recreatePtnCellBlockage

       <ptnName>
              Specifies the partition to recreate the cell blockage.

              Default: All partitions

              Data_type: string, optional

       -noPinCutSpace
              Specifies that no cut space will be created for pins in the par-
              tition cell blockage.

              Note: Blockages are always cut for power pins.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -hasPinCutSpace
              Specifies that cut space will be created for pins in the  parti-
              tion cell blockage.

              Note: This is the default.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -noViaCutSpace
              Specifies that no cut space will be created for vias in the par-
              tition cell blockage.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -hasViaCutSpace
              Specifies  that cut space will be created for vias in the parti-
              tion cell blockage.

              Note: This is the default.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command recreates pin  blockages  for  partition
                EUG:

                recreatePtnCellBlockage EUG

Related Information
              * editPin

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

